    • Method Detail

      • extract

        public static final <T extends Throwable> Optional<T> extract(@Nullable
                                                              Throwable t,
                                                              Class<T> extract)
        Extracts a Throwable of type extract from t and its cause chain. This method returns empty Optional if t isn't of type extract and there is no extract among its suppressed Throwables and causes. If there are multiple causes of type extract(java.lang.Throwable, java.lang.Class<T>) among suppressed Throwables or in the cause chain then the closest one to t in the cause chain is returned.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type of a Throwable to extract.
        Parameters:
        t - Throwable from which to extract a Throwable of type extract.
        extract - An instance of Class that represents type of a Throwable to extract.
        Returns:
        Optional with extracted Throwable of type extract or null.
